    <div class="container">
        <h1>📊 KiliVelocity Price Change Scoring System</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Complete Guide with Examples & Excel Template</p>
        
        <!-- Section 1: Overview -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>🎯 What is Price Change Scoring?</h2>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                The Price Change criterion measures how much the market has moved over your specified time period 
                (<span class="highlight">PriceStorageSeconds</span>) compared to your trigger threshold 
                (<span class="highlight">TriggerPips</span>).
            </p>
            <div class="note">
                <strong>Key Concept:</strong> A score of 5 means the market moved at least 95% of your TriggerPips threshold, 
                indicating strong momentum and a high-quality trade setup.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 2: The Formula -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>🧮 The Calculation Formula</h2>
            <div class="formula-box">
                <div class="formula">Price Change Percentage = (Actual Movement / TriggerPips) × 100</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="steps">
                <h3>Step-by-Step Calculation:</h3>
                <div class="step">
                    <strong>Step 1:</strong> EA stores prices every minute in PriceBuffer array
                </div>
                <div class="step">
                    <strong>Step 2:</strong> Calculate movement: <code>Latest Price - Oldest Price</code>
                </div>
                <div class="step">
                    <strong>Step 3:</strong> Convert to pips: <code>Movement / Point</code>
                </div>
                <div class="step">
                    <strong>Step 4:</strong> Calculate percentage: <code>(Pips / TriggerPips) × 100</code>
                </div>
                <div class="step">
                    <strong>Step 5:</strong> Assign score based on percentage thresholds
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 3: Scoring Table -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>📈 Scoring Thresholds</h2>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Price Change %</th>
                        <th>Score</th>
                        <th>Quality</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>≥ 95%</td>
                        <td class="score-5">5</td>
                        <td>🟢 Excellent</td>
                        <td>Strong momentum, high-quality setup</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>85% - 94%</td>
                        <td class="score-4">4</td>
                        <td>🔵 Good</td>
                        <td>Good momentum, acceptable setup</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>75% - 84%</td>
                        <td class="score-3">3</td>
                        <td>🟡 Fair</td>
                        <td>Moderate momentum, marginal setup</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>&lt; 75%</td>
                        <td class="score-0">0</td>
                        <td>🔴 Poor</td>
                        <td>Weak momentum, rejected trade</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>

