        <!-- Section 6: How EA Uses This -->
        <div class="section">
            <h2>⚙️ How Your EA Uses This Score</h2>
            <div class="steps">
                <div class="step">EA calculates Price Change Score for both BUY and SELL directions</div>
                <div class="step">This score is combined with other criteria (Candle Type, Close In Line, IXPower)</div>
                <div class="step">Weighted average creates Total Score (default weight = 1.0)</div>
                <div class="step">If Total Score ≥ MinTradeScore (default 4.0), trade is allowed</div>
                <div class="step">If Total Score &lt; MinTradeScore, trade is rejected</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="note">
                <strong>Example:</strong> If MinTradeScore = 4.0 and Price Change Score = 3, other criteria must average 
                above 4.5 to compensate, or the trade will be rejected.
            </div>
        </div>

